resource.name: Sales Tax Allocation, City-County Comparison Summary
resource.description: Sales tax allocation comparison summary reports present data on monthly local sales and use tax payments to local jurisdictions. These payments represent funds identified for local jurisdictions since the previous month’s distribution. When used with other local indicators, these reports may help indicate present and future economic trends. This table lists entities alphabetically by county name, then alphabetically by cities within the county.
columns_description: The payment sent to the local entity this period.
The local entity’s current sales tax rate.
The total of payments sent to the local entity in the prior calendar year to date.
The month of the local entity received the payment.
The total of payments sent to the local entity this calendar year to date.
The payment we sent to the local entity in the same period last year.
The year the local entity received the payment.
Frequency of the report.
The percent change in current payment(s) compared to the payment sent in the same period last year.
The percent change in current year payments compared to the previous year’s payments to date.
